cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with low resolution image classification and proposes a deep learning-based method for feature transfer. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper uses a pre-trained convolutional neural network (convenet) and a support vector machine (SVM) classifier for learning. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes an unsupervised method for feature transfer, which can be considered as a form of knowledge transfer in AI. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper deals with image classification and feature extraction, which are common tasks in multimedia analysis. 
5. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a possible category as the paper deals with feature transfer, which can be useful for improving the performance of image retrieval systems.
